            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>[(L) In Christi nomine]. Breve pro modernis et fucturis temporibus
                        securitatis ac firmi[ta]te ad memoriam ab[en]dam vel retinendam qualiter
                        [in] loco <placeName ref="#places/3200"
                            key="#Count #Countess #Viscount #Monasteries"><orgName
                                ref="#juridical_persons/3200" key="#Monasteries"
                            >Ficiclo</orgName></placeName> iuxta ecclesiam <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterii</rs>. Ibidem presentja <rs key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines"
                            >bonorum hominum</rs>, quorum [nomina] subter leguntur. <persName
                            key="#Countess" ref="#people/3209">Cecili[a</persName>
                        <rs key="#Countess">co]mitissa</rs> relicta q[uond]am <persName key="#Count"
                            ref="#people/3201">Ugonis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs> et <persName key="#Viscount"
                            ref="#people/3205">Ugo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Viscount">vicecomes</rs> et <persName><name ref="Wilicius"
                                >Vuilicione</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Albertus"
                                >Albertus</name></persName> filius quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Villanus">Villani</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Rainerius">Rainerius</name></persName> filius quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Vitalis">Vitali</name></persName> et
                                <persName><name ref="Gherardus">Gerardus</name></persName> fi[lius]
                        quondam <persName><name ref="Carbo">Carboni</name></persName> per virgam,
                        quam in suis detinebant manibus investierunt [at]que refutaverunt in
                        ma[nibus] <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/3210">Rodulfi</persName>
                        Lucensi <rs key="#Bishops">ep[iscopi]</rs> et <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/3211">Rugheri</persName> Volterrensi episcopi et <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/3212">Ildebrandi</persName> Pistoriensi
                        episcopi et <rs key="#Canons">canonico[rum]</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/2" key="#Canons">Florentie</placeName>, scilicet
                        preposit[i …] <rs key="#Priests">presbiteri</rs> et <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >archidiaconi</rs>, et <persName><name ref="Rodelandus">Rolandi</name>
                            de <placeName>Renonica</placeName></persName> pro episcopo Pisano, omnes
                        casa et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs> et res ec[clesi]asticas
                        qua[s] pred[ictus Ugo] comes abuit et detinuit sive iuste sive iniuste sive
                        vivere sive moreretur, que fuerunt de a[li]qua ecclesia […]bus absque aliquo
                        tenore sicut predictus Ugo comes iudicaverat in illa infirmitate de [qua
                        mortuus fuit] comitissa et Ugo vicecomes et Vuilicione et Albertus et
                        Rainerius et Gerard[us ……] predictos episcopos et canonicos et Rolandum pro
                        episcopo Pisano de medietate de omnibus cas[… …]as seu curiis et […]as
                        predictus Ugo comes abuit infra predictos <rs key="#Dioecesis"
                            >episcopatus</rs>, excepto iuris uxoris sue et <rs key="#Armed_group"
                            >militibus</rs> et servis su[…] alias legitur eo modo si predicta
                        Cecilia abuerit filium vel filiam de predicto Ugon[e] comite essem inanis et
                        va[…] et si filium vel filiam non abuerit sicut supra legitur, tunc predicta
                        Ceci&lt;li>a abeat de onnibus predictis rebus [usum]fructum donec lectum
                        mari&lt;ti> sui casto ordine observaverit sicut predictus Ugo comes
                        iudicavit et confir[ma]vit in ea infirmitate in qua mortuus fuit. Tunc
                        predicta Cecilia et Vuilicione et Rainerius et Gerardus [et] Ugo vicecomes
                        et Albertus quondam Villani et miserunt eos in manibus predicti Rodulfi
                        Lucensi episcopi ut inve[…] ipsum episcopum et predicta Cecilia et Ugo
                        vicecomes et Vuilicione et Rainerius et Gerardus […] <persName><name
                                ref="Gherardus">Geradus</name></persName> filius quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Hugo de Catignano">Ughi de <placeName
                                    ref="#places/3205">Catignano</placeName></name></persName>
                        miserunt in manibus Rugheri episcopi Volterrensi ut investiret eum […
                        aprende]runt Rainerius filius quondam Vitali miserunt in manibus canonicorum
                        Florentie ut investiret [ap]premderu[nt] <persName><name ref="Hugo"
                                >Ugo</name></persName> quondam <persName><name ref="Duodus"
                                >Duodi</name></persName> miserunt in manibus Ildeprandi episcopi
                        Pistorensi ut investiret […] <rs key="#Judge">iudicis</rs> sacri palatii
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Fraolmus">Fralmi</name></persName>,
                                <persName><name ref="Hubaldus">Ubaldi</name></persName> causarum,
                                <persName><name ref="Allucius">Alluci</name></persName> filii
                        quondam item <persName><name ref="Allucius">Alluci</name></persName>,
                        predicto Ughi filii […]. Hoc factum est anno dominice incarnationis
                        millesimo centesimo tertjodecimo, decimo kalendas mar[tii], indictione
                        sext[…]. </ab>
